This paper deals with the development and evaluation of a moral lexicon and its application in predicting moral foundations in text. This falls under the domain of computational linguistics (cs.CL) as it involves the analysis of language and its use in conveying moral values. The paper also utilizes machine learning techniques such as logistic regression and deep learning (cs.AI, cs.LG) to predict moral foundations. Additionally, the paper discusses the crowdsourcing of numeric assessments, which falls under the category of social computing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of social and political issues, which could be classified under the sub-category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
